eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu reports live from the march. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Young Nurses Indaba Trade Union is calling on government to absorb the additional healthcare workers hired to help fight the COVID-19 pandemic. This comes after the Gauteng health department announced over 800 nurses and doctors will be without jobs by the end of March due to budgetary constraints. READ:Â Over 800 Bara doctors, nurses face unemployment On Wednesday, the union resolved to embark on a march to the provincial health department's office. Lerato Mthunzi said, "the march is about protecting the jobs of all those people you called heroes during COVID-19. They all left their homes to protect South Africa . Today [the] government that sent them as heroes cannot hire them, they know our hospitals are barely surviving....."